o something.\nWell, we shall look forward to seeing him tomorrow...\nI shall hope to see you in my office, young lady, and we'll review your portfolio.", '(用于 look forward to 和 hope 之类的动词前表示语气的委婉)\n嗯，我们期待着明天与他会面。\n希望你能到我办公室来，小姐，我们将审查一下你的资料。'], ['MODAL\nYou use shall when you are referring to the likely result or consequence of a particular action or situation.\nWhen big City firms cut down on their entertainments, we shall know that times really are hard...\nThis is our last chance and we shall need to take it if we are to compete and survive.', '(表示可能的结果或后果)应该，就会\n当伦敦商业区的大公司削减他们的娱乐活动开支，我们就知道世道真的变得艰难了。\n这是我们最后的机会，如果我们想要竞争并存活下来的话，就一定要抓住这次机会。']]}]